11:17.676 --> 11:20.721
your friends all depart,

11:20.763 --> 11:23.724
perhaps your volume is

11:20.763 --> 11:23.724
where we should start.

11:23.766 --> 11:24.767
[stomach rumbling]

11:24.809 --> 11:25.726
Oh, no...

11:25.768 --> 11:26.685
[gag]

11:27.770 --> 11:30.482
[whoosh]

11:30.524 --> 11:31.690
[groan]

11:31.732 --> 11:35.570
[Rarity] Zecora?

11:31.732 --> 11:35.570
Hello? Are you there?

11:35.612 --> 11:37.947
I can't let rarity

11:35.612 --> 11:37.947
see me like this!

11:37.989 --> 11:39.698
Please don't let

11:37.989 --> 11:39.698
her know i'm here!

11:41.535 --> 11:42.619
[knocking]

11:42.661 --> 11:43.744
[door opens]

11:43.786 --> 11:44.912
Oh, dear.

11:44.954 --> 11:48.749
I'm talking even louder

11:44.954 --> 11:48.749
than I thought, aren't I?

11:48.791 --> 11:51.752
I have volume concerns

11:48.791 --> 11:51.752
today by the scores,

11:51.794 --> 11:55.382
but it seems that I'm ready

11:51.794 --> 11:55.382
to help you with yours.

11:55.423 --> 11:58.801
I'm sorry. I can't seem

11:55.423 --> 11:58.801
to hear anything.

11:58.843 --> 12:02.763
I was hoping you could help.

12:03.598 --> 12:05.766
I have no idea

12:03.598 --> 12:05.766
what happened.

12:05.808 --> 12:09.770
One minute I was sewing

12:05.808 --> 12:09.770
Phoenix feathers onto a dress

12:09.812 --> 12:13.774
and the next, I couldn't

12:09.812 --> 12:13.774
hear my own voice.

12:13.816 --> 12:17.778
Ah, the feathers of that bird

12:13.816 --> 12:17.778
can affect pony's ears.

12:17.820 --> 12:21.658
It's a magic ailment

12:17.820 --> 12:21.658
I've treated for years.

12:21.700 --> 12:22.825
I only know you're talking

12:22.867 --> 12:25.537
because your mouth is

12:22.867 --> 12:25.537
going up and down.

12:25.579 --> 12:26.787
[sigh]

12:26.829 --> 12:28.789
[sniffing]

12:28.831 --> 12:29.583
[cough]

12:29.624 --> 12:30.875
Agh! Oh, goodness!

12:30.917 --> 12:32.919
I hope that incredibly

12:30.917 --> 12:32.919
pungent odor

12:32.960 --> 12:36.631
belongs to some sort

12:32.960 --> 12:36.631
of magical curative!

12:36.673 --> 12:40.885
I hope you're not busy, but

12:36.673 --> 12:40.885
I must have my hearing back.

12:40.927 --> 12:43.804
It turns out that I talk

12:40.927 --> 12:43.804
to myself while I sew

12:43.846 --> 12:48.017
and without that conversation,

12:43.846 --> 12:48.017
I simply can't think!

12:48.059 --> 12:51.605
It's a simple cure and

12:48.059 --> 12:51.605
the directions are clear,

12:51.646 --> 12:55.400
just one or two drops

12:51.646 --> 12:55.400
in each of your ears.

12:55.816 --> 12:57.569
Oh, thank you!

12:57.611 --> 12:58.819
You're an ear saver.

12:58.861 --> 13:03.450
Oh! And while I am here, do

12:58.861 --> 13:03.450
you have any blemish cream?

13:03.491 --> 13:06.494
Spike is having

13:03.491 --> 13:06.494
some scale issues.

13:06.536 --> 13:08.787
[Spike] You

13:06.536 --> 13:08.787
have no idea.

13:11.416 --> 13:12.626
I think I heard something.

13:12.667 --> 13:15.836
Your cure is working already!

13:15.878 --> 13:18.923
The cream that you

13:15.878 --> 13:18.923
want is just over here,

13:18.965 --> 13:24.011
It's a popular potion for

13:18.965 --> 13:24.011
all creatures this year.

13:24.053 --> 13:25.722
Ah, thank you, Zecora.

13:31.645 --> 13:33.854
I don't mean to be rude,

13:33.896 --> 13:37.816
But I do think your hut

13:33.896 --> 13:37.816
could use an airing out.

13:39.902 --> 13:44.865
Rarity's gone, there's

13:39.902 --> 13:44.865
no need to hide,

13:44.907 --> 13:47.868
[sniff] Agh!

13:47.910 --> 13:51.830
Though I wonder if we

13:47.910 --> 13:51.830
should continue outside?

13:52.915 --> 13:55.627
Can't treat your symptoms

13:52.915 --> 13:55.627
down there on the ground.

13:55.669 --> 13:58.379
It's safe to come out,

13:55.669 --> 13:58.379
there's no ponies around.

13:58.421 --> 13:59.880
I'm not hiding from ponies.

13:59.922 --> 14:01.966
I'm hiding from that!

14:02.008 --> 14:03.968
[adventure music]

14:04.010 --> 14:04.885
[screech]

14:04.927 --> 14:07.305
♪♪

14:10.809 --> 14:11.810
[screech]

14:12.935 --> 14:13.852
[crash]

14:15.396 --> 14:16.939
Did I forget to mention the

14:15.396 --> 14:16.939
molt smell attracts predators?

14:16.981 --> 14:19.900
That's something that would

14:16.981 --> 14:19.900
have been quite nice to know,

14:19.942 --> 14:22.903
But it's not worth discussing

14:19.942 --> 14:22.903
right now, we should go!

14:22.945 --> 14:24.864
[screech]

14:24.905 --> 14:25.740
[crash]

14:26.949 --> 14:28.785
[screech]

14:28.827 --> 14:32.121
♪♪

14:32.163 --> 14:33.247
It's only after me!

14:33.289 --> 14:34.915
I'll lead it away

14:33.289 --> 14:34.915
while you get help!

14:37.627 --> 14:39.920
This way birdy, bird!

14:39.962 --> 14:42.549
Molting dragon over here!

14:47.804 --> 14:50.056
OK, maybe this

14:47.804 --> 14:50.056
wasn't a good plan!

14:50.097 --> 14:53.643
You can't hide in a tree,

14:50.097 --> 14:53.643
you have to come down,

14:53.685 --> 14:56.521
We stand a much better

14:53.685 --> 14:56.521
chance on the ground!

14:58.064 --> 14:59.023
[shout]

14:59.065 --> 15:00.107
Zecora!

15:00.149 --> 15:01.942
Bring her back!

15:01.984 --> 15:03.444
Agh!

15:05.697 --> 15:07.615
[screech]

15:07.657 --> 15:08.700
[panting]

15:08.742 --> 15:09.784
[thud]

15:09.826 --> 15:11.911
Oh, Spike, what are

15:09.826 --> 15:11.911
you doing here?

15:11.952 --> 15:13.954
Rarity, you have

15:11.952 --> 15:13.954
to get out of here;

15:13.996 --> 15:15.749
there's a giant Roc

15:13.996 --> 15:15.749
trying to eat me.

15:15.790 --> 15:16.875
It's got Zecora!

15:16.916 --> 15:17.709
Yes.

15:17.751 --> 15:18.959
What?

15:19.001 --> 15:22.463
I was just at zecora's,

15:19.001 --> 15:22.463
but I'm heading back.

15:22.505 --> 15:25.132
I can't read these instructions.

15:25.174 --> 15:29.970
Does this say two drops once a

15:25.174 --> 15:29.970
day, or one drop twice a day?

15:30.012 --> 15:32.973
Rarity, there's no time!

15:30.012 --> 15:32.973
We have to get help!

15:33.015 --> 15:36.977
Yes, my ears are

15:33.015 --> 15:36.977
completely clogged!

15:37.019 --> 15:39.980
Why Spike, your stone

15:37.019 --> 15:39.980
scales look worse!

15:40.022 --> 15:42.525
Oh, here, I picked

15:40.022 --> 15:42.525
up just the thing.

15:42.567 --> 15:43.568
[screech]

15:43.610 --> 15:47.697
[Rarity screams]

15:47.739 --> 15:51.701
Oh, I wish you'd escaped

15:47.739 --> 15:51.701
either claw of this bird,

15:51.743 --> 15:54.495
but the both of us trapped

15:51.743 --> 15:54.495
in the same one's absurd!

15:55.037 --> 15:55.955
What?

15:57.957 --> 15:59.959
Let my ponies go!

16:03.963 --> 16:05.548
Whoa!

16:05.590 --> 16:06.132
[stomach growls]

16:06.173 --> 16:07.216
[whoosh]

16:07.258 --> 16:09.009
[Spike screams]

16:09.051 --> 16:09.969
Agh!

16:14.056 --> 16:15.850
Aaaaaah!

16:17.727 --> 16:21.063
[pained groans]

16:21.105 --> 16:24.150
Spike? What are

16:21.105 --> 16:24.150
you doing?

16:24.191 --> 16:26.945
If my stone scales

16:24.191 --> 16:26.945
didn't itch so much

16:26.986 --> 16:28.655
and we weren't in

16:26.986 --> 16:28.655
immediate danger,

16:28.696 --> 16:31.991
this would be really

16:28.696 --> 16:31.991
embarrassing.

16:32.408 --> 16:33.242
Danger?

16:33.284 --> 16:34.577
[bird screeches]

16:41.083 --> 16:44.044
I was headed to Zecora's to

16:41.083 --> 16:44.044
get some cream for your scales.

16:44.086 --> 16:45.212
I had no idea you were--

16:46.213 --> 16:49.008
About to be eaten by

16:46.213 --> 16:49.008
a giant predator

16:49.049 --> 16:50.718
attracted to my molt smell?

16:50.760 --> 16:51.970
Molt smell?

16:52.011 --> 16:53.137
[screech]

16:53.179 --> 16:55.139
[Rarity screams] Twilight!

16:55.181 --> 16:56.933
Was that Rarity?

16:56.975 --> 16:58.392
And Zecora.

16:58.434 --> 17:00.478
I tried to save them, but it's

16:58.434 --> 17:00.478
all I can do to stop scratching

17:00.520 --> 17:03.606
long enough to dive out of the

17:00.520 --> 17:03.606
way when that bird attacks!

17:05.149 --> 17:09.153
[zaps]

17:09.195 --> 17:12.072
This isn't the first time

17:09.195 --> 17:12.072
I've been in the clutches

17:12.114 --> 17:16.076
of a horrible giant creature,

17:12.114 --> 17:16.076
but it doesn't get any easier!

17:16.118 --> 17:17.119
[sobbing]

17:25.169 --> 17:27.755
Ah! Finally!

17:27.797 --> 17:30.008
I didn't think that

17:27.797 --> 17:30.008
itching would ever stop.

17:30.049 --> 17:36.096
[crackling]

17:36.138 --> 17:37.139
What's happening?

17:37.181 --> 17:39.058
I can't mo--

17:42.896 --> 17:48.108
[zapping in the distance]

17:48.150 --> 17:51.738
[crackling]

17:51.779 --> 17:58.786
♪♪

17:59.829 --> 18:02.122
What just happened?

18:02.164 --> 18:04.333
Did I just sprout wings?

18:04.375 --> 18:06.878
I just sprouted wings!

18:06.920 --> 18:13.927
[zapping and screeching]

18:15.177 --> 18:17.638
[gasp] I've gotta help them!

18:17.680 --> 18:21.141
♪♪

18:21.183 --> 18:22.518
Whoa!

18:25.939 --> 18:27.189
[thud]

18:27.231 --> 18:28.608
[panicked shouts]

18:34.196 --> 18:35.531
Oops!

18:37.742 --> 18:40.286
Spike? How did

18:37.742 --> 18:40.286
you get wings?

18:40.327 --> 18:41.495
I don't know!

18:41.537 --> 18:43.539
But they're pretty

18:41.537 --> 18:43.539
aweso-- whoa!

18:46.375 --> 18:47.167
[snap]

18:47.209 --> 18:49.879
[screech]

18:49.921 --> 18:51.756
Do you think you can

18:49.921 --> 18:51.756
fly up and distract him

18:51.798 --> 18:53.841
while I work on freeing

18:51.798 --> 18:53.841
Zecora and Rarity?

18:59.346 --> 19:01.181
Hey, giant chicken!

19:01.223 --> 19:04.184
If you like dragons so

19:01.223 --> 19:04.184
much, come and get me!

19:04.226 --> 19:05.144
[screech]

19:05.185 --> 19:06.020
[snap]

19:13.193 --> 19:14.403
Greetings.

19:14.445 --> 19:15.279
[screech]

19:15.321 --> 19:16.196
[snap]

19:16.238 --> 19:18.198
[rumbling]

19:18.240 --> 19:19.199
[whoosh]

19:19.241 --> 19:20.952
[Rarity screams]

19:20.994 --> 19:21.911
Spike!

19:31.796 --> 19:34.924
I know that the molt

19:31.796 --> 19:34.924
produced surprising things,

19:34.966 --> 19:39.386
but I'm glad that the last

19:34.966 --> 19:39.386
was a new pair of wings!

19:39.428 --> 19:42.890
Yes, and also I'm

19:39.428 --> 19:42.890
glad you've got wings.

19:42.932 --> 19:44.892
This is amazing.

19:44.934 --> 19:46.894
I didn't know if

19:44.934 --> 19:46.894
you'd ever get wings.

19:46.936 --> 19:48.270
I'm so happy for you.

19:48.312 --> 19:50.272
Does it have something

19:48.312 --> 19:50.272
to do with this "molt"

19:50.314 --> 19:51.190
you were talking about?

19:52.108 --> 19:55.111
[sigh] It's what's

19:52.108 --> 19:55.111
been going on with me.

19:55.153 --> 19:57.030
The break out, the fire burps.

19:57.071 --> 20:00.240
The molt is when dragons get

19:57.071 --> 20:00.240
older and start to change.

20:00.282 --> 20:03.202
I wish I could stop

20:00.282 --> 20:03.202
it, but I can't.

20:03.243 --> 20:04.954
I should go.

20:05.872 --> 20:08.374
Go? What are you

20:05.872 --> 20:08.374
talking about?

20:08.415 --> 20:11.460
In the Dragonlands, families

20:08.415 --> 20:11.460
make molters leave home.

20:11.502 --> 20:13.420
It's called the Molt Effect.

20:13.462 --> 20:17.008
Well, this isn't the Dragonlands

20:13.462 --> 20:17.008
and Molt Effect or no,

20:17.050 --> 20:19.426
I don't want you going anywhere.

20:19.468 --> 20:21.261
But I'm growing up.

20:21.303 --> 20:23.347
What if something

20:21.303 --> 20:23.347
even worse happens?

20:23.389 --> 20:26.559
You're supposed to grow up,

20:23.389 --> 20:26.559
but you'll always be you.

20:26.600 --> 20:29.854
And whatever happens, we'll

20:26.600 --> 20:29.854
get through it together.

20:33.107 --> 20:37.403
Woohoo! Yeah! Look at

20:33.107 --> 20:37.403
me! Let's go home!

20:37.444 --> 20:40.948
Uh, I don't need to

20:37.444 --> 20:40.948
carry you anymore, do I?

20:40.990 --> 20:42.282
You have wings.

20:42.324 --> 20:43.201
They are new!

20:43.242 --> 20:44.911
And I don't

20:43.242 --> 20:44.911
wanna overdo it.

20:44.952 --> 20:46.412
[groan]

20:46.453 --> 20:50.290
♪♪

20:50.332 --> 20:53.293
I can't believe you thought

20:50.332 --> 20:53.293
any of us would send you away

20:53.335 --> 20:55.379
because of some

20:53.335 --> 20:55.379
silly "Molt Effect."

20:57.131 --> 20:59.508
Even if the symptoms

20:57.131 --> 20:59.508
were slightly unsettling,

20:59.550 --> 21:02.302
and let's face it, the

20:59.550 --> 21:02.302
odor wasn't pleasant,

21:02.344 --> 21:04.304
nopony would stop

21:02.344 --> 21:04.304
caring for you

21:04.346 --> 21:06.473
just because you

21:04.346 --> 21:06.473
were getting older.

21:06.515 --> 21:08.308
Everypony goes

21:06.515 --> 21:08.308
through changes.

21:08.350 --> 21:11.187
Sometimes change

21:08.350 --> 21:11.187
can be wonderful.

21:11.229 --> 21:14.481
Like being able to model

21:11.229 --> 21:14.481
for any length of dress.

21:14.523 --> 21:15.357
[giggle]

21:15.399 --> 21:18.152
A bit higher darling, please.

21:18.194 --> 21:20.905
I'm glad to help, Rarity,

21:18.194 --> 21:20.905
but don't you think there's

21:20.947 --> 21:24.117
wonderful things about flying

21:20.947 --> 21:24.117
that don't involve dresses?

21:24.158 --> 21:25.534
Of course, darling.

21:25.576 --> 21:29.247
Flying will also be beneficial

21:25.576 --> 21:29.247
for you to help me with gowns,

21:29.288 --> 21:30.539
frocks, robes, shifts,

21:29.288 --> 21:30.539
skirts, minis, maxis.

21:30.581 --> 21:32.291
[groan]

21:34.376 --> 21:37.379
♪♪
